================================================================================
Third-party software and derivations
================================================================================

1. scx_bpfland  (sched_ext/scx)  —  GPL-2.0
   https://github.com/sched-ext/scx
   Copyright (c) 2024 Andrea Righi <andrea.righi@linux.dev>

   The files under integrations/bpfland/ are a DERIVATIVE WORK of scx_bpfland:
     - integrations/bpfland/main.bpf.c.orig  is the unmodified upstream
       scx_bpfland BPF scheduler source (the eval's vanilla baseline).
     - integrations/bpfland/main.bpf.c       is that source plus the Prism
       identity-bus retrofit (a read of the shared prism_identity map mapped to
       bpfland's own deadline knob as a one-sided priority floor).
     - integrations/bpfland/main.bpf.c.replace is an earlier ablation variant.
   All three retain the upstream GPL-2.0 license and Andrea Righi's copyright
   header, as required for a GPL-2.0 derivative. The Prism additions are
   contributed under GPL-2.0.

2. sched_ext / scx tooling  —  GPL-2.0
   https://github.com/sched-ext/scx  (pinned at v1.1.0 for the 6.17 build)
   bpf/scx_prism.bpf.c is an original Prism sched_ext scheduler written against
   the scx BPF API; it is GPL-2.0 (it uses GPL-only kernel helpers and declares
   SEC("license") = "GPL").

3. libbpf  —  LGPL-2.1 OR BSD-2-Clause
   https://github.com/libbpf/libbpf
   bpf/include/bpf/ contains a MINIMAL LOCAL SHIM of a few libbpf macro/helper
   prototypes, used only to let the BPF objects compile on a host without
   libbpf-dev. On any host with libbpf-dev the real system headers are used
   instead. The shim reimplements (does not copy) the small subset of the libbpf
   API that the Prism BPF programs include.

4. iovisor/bcc execsnoop (libbpf-tools)  —  Apache-2.0 / GPL-2.0
   https://github.com/iovisor/bcc
   bpf/consumers/execsnoop_prism.bpf.c follows the structure of the well-known
   execsnoop tracer (two execve tracepoints, per-pid stash, perf-event output)
   and adds the Prism identity read; it is GPL-2.0.

The Kubernetes client (k8s.io/client-go) and the eBPF Go library (cilium/ebpf)
are used as ordinary Go module dependencies under their own licenses; see go.mod
and the module cache for the authoritative texts.
